data.name: Nabilla
data.bio: French-Swiss social media influencer, entrepreneur, and reality TV personality based in Dubai. Known for lifestyle, beauty, and family content.

products.name: Nabilla Beauty
products.description: Nabilla Beauty is Nabilla Vergara's own makeup brand, launched in 2018, offering a range of cruelty-free beauty products such as matte liquid lipsticks, glosses, eyeliners, palettes, mascaras, blushes, and highlighters, designed for all skin tones and made in Italy.[1][2]

products.name: Bitcoin Promotion (Sponsorship)
products.description: Nabilla Vergara was involved in a major paid sponsorship promoting Bitcoin to her followers on Snapchat, which became highly significant due to its large reach and subsequent regulatory attention in France.[3]

data.name: Lena Mahfouf
data.bio: Léna Mahfouf, known as Léna Situations, is a French-Algerian lifestyle, fashion, and entrepreneurship influencer. She is renowned for her authentic vlogs, fashion inspiration, and positive engagement with her audience.

products.name: Hôtel Mahfouf
products.description: Léna Mahfouf's own clothing and lifestyle brand, launched in June 2022, featuring fashion items, lifestyle products, and pop-up retail experiences such as cafés and themed stores in Paris. It blends fashion, hospitality, and creative expression, making it her signature entrepreneurial venture.

products.name: Dior
products.description: Major luxury brand partnership; Léna Mahfouf is a 'friend of the house' for Dior, creating frequent sponsored content and attending high-profile events like Paris Fashion Week. Her collaboration generated significant media impact and positioned her as a top influencer in the fashion industry.

data.name: Marie Lopez
data.bio: Marie Lopez, known as EnjoyPhoenix, is a leading French digital creator and influencer specializing in beauty, lifestyle, and wellness content. She is based in Paris and is recognized for her authentic advice and entrepreneurial ventures.

products.name: Leaves and Clouds
products.description: Marie Lopez's own brand, launched in 2018, offering a curated selection of lifestyle, home decor, zero-waste beauty, hygiene, grocery, and stationery products, with a focus on items made in France and Europe, emphasizing nature and sustainability.

products.name: Lashilé Beauty (Hair Gummies Promotion)
products.description: Marie Lopez has a major partnership with Lashilé Beauty, promoting their clinically proven, sugar-free hair growth and strengthening gummies, which are designed to support hair health and are easy to take.

data.name: Hugo Hilaire
data.bio: French dancer and content creator known for viral TikTok dance videos and sharing selfies and lifestyle content on Instagram.

products.name: Hugo Hilaire Green Screen Meme Template
products.description: A digital green screen template featuring Hugo Hilaire dancing to a viral Brazilian song, used by fans and creators for meme content and video edits.

products.name: Fitout Clothing Collaboration
products.description: A clothing collaboration promoted by Hugo Hilaire, featuring casual wear and accessories, often showcased in his TikTok dance videos and worn by other influencers.

data.name: Cédric Grolet
data.bio: World-renowned French pastry chef known for trompe-l'œil patisserie and viral dessert creations. Shares recipes, behind-the-scenes, and pastry art.

products.name: Cédric Grolet Fruits Sculptés
products.description: Hyper-realistic pastries crafted to look like real fruits, featuring chocolate shells and fruit-based mousses and jellies. These signature desserts are sold in Grolet's boutiques in Paris, London, and Monaco, and are internationally recognized for their artistry and flavor.

products.name: La Pâtisserie du Meurice par Cédric Grolet
products.description: Flagship pastry boutique located at Le Meurice hotel in Paris, offering Grolet's iconic trompe-l'œil desserts, viennoiseries, and entremets. The boutique is a destination for his most famous creations and seasonal specialties.
